## Creating a Vector Bucket

```
Supabase Dashboard → Storage → New Bucket
  Type: Vector Bucket
  Name: embeddings
  Public: false (vector buckets should always be private)
```

Then create an index:
```
Dashboard → Storage → [your bucket] → Create Index
  Name: documents-index
  Dimensions: 1536  (match your embedding model exactly)
  Distance metric: cosine  (recommended for text embeddings)
  Index type: HNSW  (better accuracy) or Flat (exact, for <100K vectors)
```

```typescript
// Programmatically create a bucket and index (in migration or seed)
const { data, error } = await supabase.storage.createBucket('embeddings', {
  public: false,
})

// Index creation is currently dashboard-only in Public Alpha
// Store the index name for use in your code
const INDEX_NAME = 'documents-index'
const BUCKET_NAME = 'embeddings'
```

