## Metadata Filtering

Metadata fields act as pre-filters before similarity search — much faster than
filtering after search.

```typescript
// Store with rich metadata
await storeVectors([{
  key: 'doc-123',
  embedding: [...],
  metadata: {
    user_id: userId,              // string
    category: 'legal',            // string enum
    created_at: '2026-01-15',     // ISO date string
    is_public: false,             // boolean
    word_count: 1250,             // number
    content_preview: 'First 200 characters...',
  }
}])

// Query with metadata filter
const results = await supabase.storage
  .vectors.from(BUCKET).index(INDEX)
  .queryVectors({
    queryVector: { float32: queryEmbedding },
    topK: 5,
    filter: {
      user_id: { $eq: userId },           // equality
      category: { $in: ['legal', 'hr'] }, // in list
      word_count: { $gte: 500 },          // numeric comparison
      is_public: { $eq: true },           // boolean
    },
    returnMetadata: true,
  })
```

