## SQL Query via S3 Vector FDW

Vector Buckets can also be queried from Postgres SQL using the S3 Vectors FDW.
Useful for: analytics, hybrid queries, scheduled batch operations.

```sql
-- Enable wrappers extension (if not already)
CREATE EXTENSION IF NOT EXISTS wrappers WITH SCHEMA extensions;

-- Create S3 Vectors foreign server
CREATE SERVER vector_server
  FOREIGN DATA WRAPPER s3_vectors_wrapper
  OPTIONS (
    project_url '[YOUR_SUPABASE_URL]',
    api_key_id '[VAULT_SECRET_UUID]'   -- store anon key in Vault
  );

CREATE SCHEMA IF NOT EXISTS vectors;

CREATE FOREIGN TABLE vectors.documents (
  key TEXT,
  embedding VECTOR(1536),
  metadata JSONB
)
SERVER vector_server
OPTIONS (
  bucket_name 'embeddings',
  index_name 'documents-index'
);

-- Similarity search from SQL (uses <===> operator — different from pgvector's <=>)
SELECT key, metadata, embedding <===> '[0.1, 0.2, ...]'::VECTOR AS distance
FROM vectors.documents
ORDER BY distance
LIMIT 5;

-- Hybrid query: join vector results with Postgres data
SELECT d.key, p.title, p.created_at,
       d.embedding <===> query_emb AS similarity
FROM vectors.documents d
JOIN public.posts p ON p.id::TEXT = d.key
ORDER BY similarity DESC
LIMIT 10;
```

---

## Distance Metrics

```
cosine     — recommended for text embeddings (OpenAI, Cohere, etc.)
             Measures angle between vectors, ignores magnitude
             Score: 0 = identical, 2 = opposite

euclidean  — for spatial/numeric data
             Measures actual distance in vector space
             Score: 0 = identical, higher = more different

l2         — alias for euclidean (same thing, different name)
             Use either — they produce identical results
```

